Of course it is wrong. ASL started to develop when an American school
for deaf people taught its pupils French sign language. This was mixed
among the pupils with their natural sign languages - such as the one
which naturally evolved in Martha's Vineyard, where there was a big
community of deaf people, because one of the founders of the place
happened to be deaf - for genetic, hereditary reasons. The sign
language which naturally evolved from this mixture is called ASL.
