University Publications, Uralic and Altaic Series, Vol. 45. Page 225 -
Appendix II: The Standard Dialect of Soviet Azerbaijan)

I only add, that in the era of mass literacy and mass alphabetization,
written usage and spelling do exert a massive influence even upon
colloquial usage, especially through prepared speech in the media and
in public announcements. Of course, this concerns mostly languages
which have a moderately phonetic spelling, such as Finnish.
